# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# its 73RD LANGUAGE — Pyret.  Pyret joins the corpus as a single-
# instance language (Pyret=1) via the canonical `pyret` CLI binary
# using 75lb/command-line-args + command-line-usage for argv parsing.
# Taxonomy now spans 300 cross-language CLI library variants across
# 73 documented languages.
#
# **R561 IS A ROUND-NUMBER MILESTONE — TAXONOMY CROSSES 300 VARIANTS.**
# The round-sequence R500-R561 has added 298 CLI library variants and
# 66 language entries.  Crossing 300 means the corpus now documents
# CLI library variants at a density approaching 4.2 per language
# (300/72 from R560 → 300/73 = 4.11 per language).
#
# Leaderboard unchanged: Rust=47 / Go=47 / TS-Node=47 (three-way tie
# at 47 preserved from R560).  Pyret=1 (new — 73rd language entry).
#
# This is the SECOND documented PEDAGOGICAL PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE in
# the taxonomy.  The FIRST was Logtalk R533 (designed for declarative
